episodes.title: Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor arrested on suspicion of misconduct in public office | Newstalk
episodes.description:
The former Prince Andrew, the King's brother, has been arrested on suspicion of misconduct in public office.

It's his 66th birthday.

Allegations emerged he'd sent Jeffrey Epstein sensitive information while working as a trade envoy.

He's always denied wrongdoing in connection with his links to the late paedophile.

Thames Valley Police officers are searching properties in Norfolk and Berkshire - and are being supported by other forces.

Unmarked police cars were seen arriving at Sandringham this morning.

Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor remains in custody.

Legal commentator Joshua Rosenberg doesn't expect him to be kept in overnight.

Buckingham Palace released a statement a few days ago, saying it stands ready to support the police, if approached.

The King stripped Andrew of his titles and home last year.
